{"lemma": "صَباحٌ", "slug": "صَباحٌ", "root": "ص.ب.ح", "root_slug": "ص-ب-ح", "root_link": "/words/roots/ص-ب-ح", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "صَباح", "root": "صبح", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 1}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 3, "pos_tags": ["adj", "noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 4}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n23641", "n23642", "n23648"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AD%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "morning", "fa": "صبح", "ur": "صبح", "tr": "sabah", "id": "pagi", "bn": "সকাল", "es": "mañana", "fr": "matin", "de": "Morgen", "ru": "утро", "zh": "早晨"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "the time from sunrise to noon, morning", "tags": ["Arabic", "Modern", "Standard"], "examples": [{"text": "صَبَاحُ الْخَيْر", "english": "Good morning"}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "the time from morning twilight to sunrise, dayspring", "tags": ["archaic"]}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "pretty, comely, handsome, graceful"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "masculine plural of صَبِيح (ṣabīḥ)", "tags": ["form-of", "masculine", "plural"]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Cognate with Ge'ez ጽበሕ (ṣəbäḥ).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."}, "ipa": ["/sˤa.baːħ/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n23641", "headword_ar": "صَبَاحٌ", "root": "SbH", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SuboHN", "text_ar": "صُبْحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b2-  Also (Msb)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "masaA='N", "text_ar": "مَسَا=ءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, A, Msb,) and so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SabiyHapN", "text_ar": "صَبِيحَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,) [and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^uSobuwHapN", "text_ar": "اُصْبُوحَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(as in a phrase following in this paragraph), and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maSobaHN", "text_ar": "مَصْبَحٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (see this last word,)] i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Morning,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "forenoon, counted from sunrise to noon:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb and TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "msw", "text_ar": "مسو"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) or, accord. to some,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from midnight to noon:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "msw", "text_ar": "مسو"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) or, accord. to the Arabs,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from the beginning of the latter half of the night to the time when the sun declines from the meridian;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "then commences the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "masaA='", "text_ar": "مَسَا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", extending to the end of the former half of the night; thus expl. by Th; so says El-Jawá- leekee. (Msb.) The Arabs say, when they regard a man, &c., as ominous of evil,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SabaAHu", "text_ar": "صَبَاحُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A@ll~`hi laA SabaAHuka", "text_ar": "ا@للّٰهِ لَا صَبَاحُكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "God's morning: not thy morning"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: and if you will, you may say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SabaAHa A@ll~`hi laA SabaAHaka", "text_ar": "صَبَاحَ ا@للّٰهِ لَا صَبَاحَكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Lh, TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eimo SabaAHFA", "text_ar": "عِمْ صَبَاحًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EimuwA SabaAHFA", "text_ar": "عِمُوا صَبَاحًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) lit. imperative, but meaning a prayer, i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "May thy life,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "your life, be pleasant during the morning,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Har p. 32, and TA * in arts."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nEm", "text_ar": "نعم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wEm", "text_ar": "وعم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) is a salutation of the people of the Time of Ignorance. (TA.) One says also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laqiytuhu SabaAHFA", "text_ar": "لَقِيتُهُ صَبَاحًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*aA SabaAHK", "text_ar": "ذَا صَبَاحٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^atayotuhu *aA SabaAHK", "text_ar": "اَتَيْتُهُ ذَا صَبَاحٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) which [i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*A SbAH", "text_ar": "ذا صباح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] is only used adverbially, (Sb, S, K,) except in the dial. of Khath'am, (Sb, S,) meaning ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I met him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I came to him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in a morning,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "between daybreak and sunrise:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) the following verse (S, TA) by Anas Ibn-Nuheyk, of Khath'am, (TA,) or, as some say, by Iyás Ibn-Mudrikeh El-Hanafee, (so in a marg. note in a copy of the S,) presents an exception to the adverbial usage:"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "Eazamotu EalaY A_iqaAmapi *iY SabaAHK\n                      \n                     \n                        liA^amorK m~aA yusaw~adu mano yasuwdu"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, TA:) the poet means,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I determined to stay until the time of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SbAH", "text_ar": "صباح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e. either"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "dawn"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "forenoon"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: for"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it is on account of some particular thing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e. some good quality, or some praiseworthy thing,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that he is made a chief who becomes a chief:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "thus Ibn-Es-Seeráfee explains this verse. (TA.) And one says, ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^atayotuhu *aA SabuwHK", "text_ar": "اَتَيْتُهُ ذَا صَبُوحٍ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", not used otherwise than adverbially, meaning the same as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*aA SabaAHK", "text_ar": "ذَا صَبَاحٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", expl. above; (K;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*aAta AlS~abuwHi", "text_ar": "ذَاتَ الصَّبُوحِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the morning,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "first part of day, before sunrise:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAar, TA:) or ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*aA SabuwHK", "text_ar": "ذَا صَبُوحٍ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[properly means]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in a time of drinking the"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "morning-draught called"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SabuwH", "text_ar": "صَبُوح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yawomi ka*aA", "text_ar": "يَوْمِ كَذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^atayotuhu SabiyHapa", "text_ar": "اَتَيْتُهُ صَبِيحَةَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I came to him in the dawn,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the morning,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "forenoon, of such a day"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (A:) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^uSobuwHapa", "text_ar": "اُصْبُوحَةَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kul~i yawomK", "text_ar": "كُلِّ يَوْمٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the morning of every day"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and in like manner,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^umosiy~apa kul~i yawomK", "text_ar": "اُمْسِيَّةَ كُلِّ يَوْمٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^atayotuhu", "text_ar": "اَتَيْتُهُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SabaAHa masaA='a", "text_ar": "صَبَاحَ مَسَا=ءَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Sb, A, TA,) for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SabaAHFA wamasaA='F", "text_ar": "صَبَاحًا وَمَسَا=ءً"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I came to him morning"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "evening,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "every morning and evening:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Sharh esh-Shudhoor, p. 31:) the two nouns are thus constructed by some of the Arabs, after the manner of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xamosapa Ea$ara", "text_ar": "خَمْسَةَ عَشَرَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": but some prefix the former noun to the other, putting the latter in the gen. case, except when the expression is used as a denotative of state, or adverbially: (TA:) [or, accord. to IHsh,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SabaAHa", "text_ar": "صَبَاحَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "masaA='K", "text_ar": "مَسَا=ءٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is allowable as [an adverbial expression] meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SabaAHa *aA masaA='K", "text_ar": "صَبَاحَ ذَا مَسَا=ءٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[lit."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in a morning having an evening,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in a forenoon having an afternoon"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and a similar instance occurs in the Kur, ch. lxxix. last verse. (Sharh esh-Shudhoor, ubi suprà.) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yawomu AlS~abaAHi", "text_ar": "يَوْمُ الصَّبَاحِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The day of the hostile,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "predatory, incursion."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, K.) The Arabs, when suddenly attacked in the morning by a troop of horsemen, cry aloud,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaA SabaAHaAho", "text_ar": "يَا صَبَاحَاهْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "O! a hostile,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "predatory, incursion!"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; warning the whole tribe: (TA:) this is said by him who calls for aid: (JM:) for they generally made a hostile, or predatory, incursion in the morning: (TA, JM:) or, as some say, the two conflicting parties used, when night came, to abstain; and when day returned, they recommenced; so that the case is as though he who said thus meant, The time of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SabaAH", "text_ar": "صَبَاح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or morning] has come, therefore prepare yourselves for fighting. (JM.)"}], "source_refs": ["Msb", "S", "A", "K", "Sb", "TA", "IAar", "JM"]}, {"entry_id": "n23642", "headword_ar": "صُبَاحٌ", "root": "SbH", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "The"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$uElap", "text_ar": "شُعلَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "lighted wick"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qinodiyl", "text_ar": "قِنْدِيل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "lamp"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (K.) [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "miSobaAHN", "text_ar": "مِصْبَاحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]       -A2-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SabiyHN", "text_ar": "صَبِيحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", q. v. (Ks, S, K.)"}], "source_refs": []}, {"entry_id": "n23648", "headword_ar": "صُبَّاحٌ", "root": "SbH", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SabiyHN", "text_ar": "صَبِيحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": []}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}